snippet.textDisplay: Two comments: First, although I was a mechanical engineer before retiring I often spent days wearing a half-face P100 respirator.  Workers in many construction and manufacturing jobs wear them (or N100 or R100) all day at their jobs.  Reasonably healthy people can do so without problems (note the "reasonably healthy" part).  Second, I'm 73, have never had a flu shot, and have not had a case of flu in more than 40 years.  I follow good hygiene as recommended by a doctor more than 40 years ago after a couple of bad experiences with intestinal viruses.  If you want a flu shot then by all means get one.  But the first line of defense, flu shot or not, is to avoid (as my doctor said four decades ago) picking it up on your hands and sticking in your eyes and nose.
